(133, 1, '2014-12-15 04:11:13', '2014-12-15 04:11:13', 'To do or not to do has been a permanent question in my life – the situation was no different when it came to deciding whether to enrol in Dynamic Mind Work’s Trainers’ Training course. I had already completed my NLP Practitioner and Master Practitioner with Robb and knew that completing these courses were two of the best decisions I had made in my life. But Trainers’ Training?\r\n\r\nPart of me knew that I had to enrol since the course would help me to progress professionally in my role as a lecturer as well as personally in my day-to-day interactions with my colleagues, my friends, and my loved ones. Still, another part of me hesitated, being fully aware that completing the course would pose yet another change to my life, yet another stretch for my mind and a journey that, once started, would leave the comfort of my current situation in the shadows far behind.\r\n\r\nIn the end my never-ending curiosity and my willingness to learn and improve myself and my life proved to be stronger than my hesitations. I enrolled – and having completed the training, I can confidently add the course to my list of best decisions made in my life. Truth be told, it was a challenging journey, but more importantly, a very rewarding and enjoyable one.\r\n\r\nAnd I know that as you are reading this you are wondering what made the course so special for me. The answer is simple. Like it is the case for most everyone, my life is about people and my relationships with them. For me this means liaising with students in the classroom, potential students and their parents and spouses at marketing events and the people close to me in my private life.\r\n\r\nAs a lecturer, one of the most important aspects is the ability to ensure that students understand and are enthused about why they are learning what they are learning and how they can incorporate it into their private and professional life. The same holds true for potential students.\r\n\r\nThrough the completion of Trainers’ Training I have gained this ability – I understand what makes my students tick and thus how to best leverage their educational experience. While I previously concentrated mostly on contents, these days my focus is on what my students value, how they learn best and on identifying what they need in order to fully grasp the concepts I teach and their relevance to them and their life. In order to do this, I need to consistently gather feedback from the classroom; observing and calibrating to find out where my students are at – yet another ability obtained as a courtesy from completing Trainers’ Training.  And I do all of this more easily, effortlessly and with a much higher degree of confidence compared to before.\r\n\r\nAt the end of the day, my private interactions are not so different compared to the ones in the classroom – bar the lecturing part, of course. In order to make conversations flow, for people to feel at ease with me and for us to have an enjoyable and productive time, the same principles apply: I need to know what is important to them, see where they are at and identify what they need. And that’s just that.\r\n\r\nI feel that since completing the course, my relationships have improved significantly – they are more enjoyable, less emotionally heated, and more constructive with much more fun and laughter. And this includes the relationship I have with myself! To me there is a clear link between the quality of the relationships I have and the quality of my life – both are on an upward trend and rising! For a big part I have to thank Robb for this. I surely could have completed my training elsewhere, but I am glad I chose to complete it with Robb. I have known Robb for about 2 years and, quite frankly, because of my more than extensive experience in teaching and learning, I tend to be a hard marker. Yet, Robb has always managed to fulfil and exceed my expectations – even at times when I was most resistant, he knew what I needed and provided it in a caring, trusting and professional manner. His ability to direct individuals and the group as required, to embed important and challenging ideas and concepts in a seemingly chit-chat manner and to run trainings smoothly and in a fun and safe way is outstanding and one of a kind. Obviously, I would recommend his courses to anyone interested in wanting more – for themselves and from life.\r\n\r\nA lot of people may think that Trainers’ Training is about presenting to small or big groups – and that’s right... but it is so much more than that. For me it was a personal and professional journey with many aha moments, sighs of relief and revelations – and I am wondering what it will be for you. One thing I do know is that if you have a list of best decisions in your life, then Trainers’ Training will make that list sooner or later.\r\n\r\nMaike', 'Maike Sundmacher', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'maikesundmacher', '', '', '2015-01-11 02:26:56', '2015-01-11 02:26:56', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.218/Robbwhitewood/php/?post_type=testimonials&#038;p=133', 0, 'testimonials', '', 0),
