(233, 1, '2015-01-03 07:02:07', '2015-01-03 07:02:07', 'I can’t begin to tell you how grateful I am to you for last night. Robb,the relationship exercise you did with me has changed my perception for the better on so many levels! I don’t know if  you realize it or not, but you also gave me back my self-esteem last night. While i was driving past RNSH on the way home  I had the epiphany  that because I was in the bubble with limitless love and joy etc ... and that love didn’t come from the the other bubbles that I don’t need to be a doormat and try to get love and validation from  any other bubbles, because I have more then enough in my own bubble!\r\n\r\nBut at the same time I don’t think I am GOD’S gift or anything, so it’s not going against my yoga training. It’s more of a total acceptance. It really was 36 years of therapy in 10 mins.   THANK YOU, THANK YOU, THANK YOU!\r\n\r\nNow i want to become a “mechanic”!!!\r\n\r\nI‘ve been  psychoanalyzing myself all night and I am pretty sure I know now why I started smoking again after 6 years of not even wanting to. It’s funny  - on Monday I wrote down a   ‘shopping  list ‘ of things I wanted to re-wire and I actually wrote “smoking-emotional?” So it was fascinating to hear about it putting you in a dissociative state and suppressing emotions.\r\n\r\nAnyway, I’d better do some work now but i just wanted you to know how grateful I am for the profound changes you’ve helped me with.\r\n\r\nNAMASTE, ALEX.', 'Alex Hulbert', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'alex-hulbert', '', '', '2015-01-15 09:42:02', '2015-01-15 09:42:02', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.218/Robbwhitewood/php/?post_type=testimonials&#038;p=233', 0, 'testimonials', '', 0),
